===Etymology 3===
''X'' is a variable which can stand for letters representing parts of speech such as: ''N'' (noun), ''V'' (verb), ''P'' (preposition), etc.
====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|grammar|X-bar theory}} {{initialism of|en|[[X]] [[phrase|Phrase]]}} {{gloss|a phrase which consists of either: (1) an optional [[specifier]] and an [[X-bar]] phrase, or (2) a [[conjunction]] [[sandwiched]] between two other XPs. The X is a "pro-letter" which can be substituted by letters such as N for noun, V for verb, P for preposition, I for inflectional, etc.}}
